# SUMMARY OF KEY CONCEPTS
# ============================================================================
summary = """
SUMMARY: DATA VISUALIZATION

1. PANDAS BASICS:
   - head()/tail() - first/last rows
   - describe() - statistics
   - sort_values() - sorting
   - groupby() - aggregation
   - merge()/concat() - combining

2. DATA CLEANING:
   - dropna() - remove missing
   - fillna() - fill missing
   - loc/iloc - indexing
   - Filtering with conditions

3. CHART TYPES:
   - Line: trends over time
   - Histogram: distribution of values
   - Scatter: relationship between 2 variables
   - Bar: category comparison
   - Pie: part-to-whole
   - Box: quartiles & outliers
   - Area: cumulative trends
   - Bubble: 3 variables

4. MATPLOTLIB:
   - plt.plot() - line
   - plt.hist() - histogram
   - plt.scatter() - scatter
   - plt.bar() - bar chart
   - plt.pie() - pie chart
   - plt.boxplot() - box plot
   - Subplots for multiple plots

5. PANDAS PLOTTING:
   - df.plot(kind="line/bar/scatter/hist/box")
   - Convenient, uses Matplotlib

6. STATISTICS:
   - var() - variance
   - corr() - correlation (-1 to 1)
   - mean(), std(), etc.

7. PLOTLY (INTERACTIVE):
   - Better for interactive dashboards
   - Supports 3D visualization
   - Hover, zoom, pan features
   - Export to HTML

8. 2D vs 3D:
   - 2D: most charts
   - 3D: when 3 variables matter visually
